original: Lindqvist, Erik Gustaf, statens lantbruksingenjör, Kalmar, f. 15/3/93 i Gävle av köpm. Gustaf Fredrik L. o. Erika Charlotta Åberg. G. 23 m. Margot Wolf. Barn: Maud f. 31, Vera 39. — Studrex. 12, avg:ex. fr. KTH 19, fr. Alnarps lantbr:inst. 20. Stat. lantbr:stip. 19. Stat. lantbr :ing. i Norrb. 1. norra del 23, i Kalmar 1. sed. 31. RVO.
translated: Lindqvist, Erik Gustaf, state agricultural engineer, Kalmar, b. 15/3/93 in Gävle, son of merchant Gustaf Fredrik L. and Erika Charlotta Åberg. Married in 1923 to Margot Wolf. Children: Maud b. 1931, Vera b. 1939. Completed secondary education, passed the exams from the Royal Institute of Technology in 1919, and completed studies at Alnarp agricultural institute in 1920. Received a state agricultural scholarship in 1919. Started working as a state agricultural engineer in the northern part of Norrbotten in 1923, and in Kalmar since 1931. Awarded with the Royal Order of Vasa.
